caption: DO NOT ORDER FROM THIS PLACE ON SEAMLESS:  I ordered at 6:50pm. Food arrived at 8:27pm. Had called restaurant at 8:10pm, they said it was on way. Upon arrival-Guacamole was all very brown and UNEDIBLE. The tacos were in a food box--upon opening looked like they were all shook around and it was just 1 big mess of lettuce and meat on 1 side of the box and the tortillas on the other. It no longer resembled tacos at all. Called the restaurant, asked for a mangager. Was told no manager. I informed them of my problems. They told me there was nothing they could do and to contact Seamless.  I can't believe this is the customer support that happens.  This is terrible service.  My food is completely unedible and all messed up.  They should send another order.

I came here with a date. They didn't have half of the food or any wine that was on the menu. Both myself and my date got sick from the food that we ordered. The waitstaff was absent for most of dinner service. Do not eat here! It has been a long time since any food in NYC has made me sick. It is absolutely not worth it!!
The food and service was excellent!!
Love their outdoor patio and fantastic food, great big pitchers of margaritas & friendly staff! Fish tacos were fantastic 👌🏼

Bad service and antiprofessional. Yesterday (Tuesday) I was here to have dinner service. Decent food and very good presentation pleasing to the eye. But the service on the part of the staff very bad, our waiter all the time with the girl bartender watching videos on the phone and giving samples of affectionate love, something that is not correct and very bad taste and offensive between employees and less in hours of service.

Stumbled upon this place with some friends on Cinco de Mayo. They had live music and specials on Margaritas. Also they have free tequila shots but you have to ask for them! Not the best Mexican food, but the duck tacos and the chicken chilaquiles verde we’re pretty good.
Happy cinqo de mayo. The margs are decent not sweet but okay. Worth a stop, the tacos ain't bad.
Just moved to the neighborhood. Now I go here every week! Really special ambiance and vibe, and delicious food that's somehow also affordable.

I just received my order. It was delivered by caviar so this is more of a bad review for that service but the food was 1 hour late, cold and the delivery guy was so out of it he put the food in his backpack sideways and then biked here. The restaurant had nothing to say but sorry and you can’t leave a review on caviars site. So disappointing and won’t order from here again or caviar. Bad all around!

This place and Mr. Andrés and his wife. It deserves to be reported and sued to the work department. For not paying and saving your employees' money.  He spends it giving checks that do not have funds. I worked there and they still owe me a lot of money.  I am sure that more than one of those who work there would be willing to support me in my battle against that place and its owner.
The food and drinks are great!

The new ownership is amazing.  Abby is amazing bartender.  She makes amazing Margs and they are $6 all day long.  Wow, i am in love again.  Great Mexican restaurant.  Highly recommend!!! The food is to die for!!!
Nice place ,las mejores margaritas the attention super good very friendly have to come.

Worst service ever. And also, bland food. I came here for brunch on a Sunday. There were only 2 other customers, the place was dead. Our waiter took our order and it took 50 mins for the food to arrive. Then the waiter disappeared for 30 mins in the bathroom. The bartender was on her phone so I had to stand up and walk across the restaurant to ask her for another drink. When the waiter came out he walked right past us (didnt ask how our food was, didnt notice we were finished) and went on his phone. I had to ask again can we get our check?! Awful!!! LAZY. Also, the food was bland. This place has never heard of SALT. Worst place EVER!
Very good chorizo tacos 🌮!

Very bad place, to start with the service. On Sunday we were there for dinner but our waiter had no respect for the customers all the time he was watching and talking on his phone. and add that when he approached the table with a bad unpleasant smell of cigarettes. and not to mention the other employees who always spend their time in a bad mood and COMPLAINING THAT THEY ARE NOT PAID AND THEY MUST A LOT OF MONEY. VERY BAD SERVICE  PD:but this is not the fault of the employees. It's really the owner or manager. My advice is to resign and sue. if that is really what happens.
The best restaurant ever ! Amazing food and great service. Love there escargots and also the steak and burgers ! Definitely coming here again !

Excellent margaritas and amazing duck tacos to go along with it. Good vibes, too.

Great food, Brunch special was 25$ for all you can drink. Yay!!! Brunch menu is great!!!! Had the banana nutella crepes and it was delicious comes with whip cream that tastes like vanilla ice cream. Definetly worth checking it out.
Randomly stumbled in from Barcade with a group of friends. Great cocktails and snacks!
Great food, eggs Benedict was fantastic. Very cozy atmosphere as well.
Went there today at 3 pm and they were closed.

They lied about the menu and they actively hid from customers. The waitress went around a corner to fiddle with her phone the whole time.  A new colleague arrived at the restaurant and saw me waiting to catch the attention of the waitress. She gossiped to the waitress for 20s then wandered off, allowing the waitress to resume her phone activities.  The menu advertised some deep-fried peppers. When they were ready, I received various finger points, guiding a waitress. I tried a few peppers, but realised they weren't that great - I questioned why I ever ordered this then realised that I hadn't; I'd ordered deep-fried peppers yet received grilled peppers.  I called the kitchen runner who proved useless and grabbed the phone waitress who played dumb and tried making out that my order was still valid. She offered some sort of alternative, but how could I trust them any more?  I'd say don't go, but I don't need to - even if you do turn up, you be hard pressed even finding the waitress and ordering a drink.
Lovely backyard
I love the vibe of this place. French + south western I think. Awesome outdoor patio and live music some nights. Good ambient place for a date!

Nice place with a very nice garden in the back. We went for brunch, food is good - not excellent but the steak and egg was delicious - and aligned with pricing.  Service was very nice and the waiter was very friendly.

In an everything neighborhood of brand new high rises, it was great to fall into this book of a bar restaurant to catch a World Cup game. There is a cozy backyard is verdant and clever wood furniture easily fit the various groups of people. The Venezuelan bartender mixed a delicious margarita for myself and sweet looking strawberry margaritas for my friends. We did not eat but the food our neighbors ordered looked delicious. The crowd was friendly, the game was close and positive vibes abounded. This is a great place that I hope survives for a long time! Come support and enjoy
Friendly staff, awesome drinks and an open mic on Sundays!!!

The ONLY negative review I've ever written about a restaurant in 40+ years...  Food used to be excellent a few years ago but quality dropped to ridiculously poor levels. Tiny frozen shrimp in a shrimp risotto for $20 is a joke. Also an etiquette-challenged prick bartender is almost hilarious, but really just groanworthy. How is this spot open? Oh yeah, thanks condos. Don't waste a cash-only (why?) dollar at this spot, plenty of good meals nearby (Regal, Barricou, Dar etc).
If you looking for a good Mexican food do not come to this place, if you are going to order ask them what they have available before you make you order
We ordered two tacos carnitas and al pastor and they didn’t have neither of them. Expensive but has a nice outdoor area.
Perfect brunch spot. Went when it was a little rainy outside, no wait, perfect food, great drinks. (Even sat outside in back garden area) Can't wait to go back again
Lovely backyard and really great food.
Old food with bugs; class B

Slow low quality food. Messed up multiple parts of the order then overcharged us twice. Planet Earth was playing on the large screen, because a leopard killing an alligator is exactly the kind of background visual you you want for brunch.
My favorite restaurant in Williamsburg! They offer delicious Mexican and French food, which is a great combination. Everything I've had there is amazing. Definitely worth the price.
I need to come back for the live music

Like the decor and atmosphere. I always get the chilaquiles for brunch. This time chilaquiles were ok. Nothing to write home about but I enjoyed the spicy level. I’d definitely go back. I think it was an off day. Service was great!

Geeze. Who would have paired lavender with jalapeños? Surprisingly delightful, but perhaps not as much as Paige’s jokes and dance moves and the movies they had playing on the projector. This was a fun and cozy spot!
Good Mexican/French restaurant, never packed, good for small groups that don't like to wait for hours for brunch/lunch/dinner..! 👌
Always love coming heree! Tacos are amazing, happy hour is great, Sunday open mics, live music on Friday and Saturday evenings, and free tarot on Monday's!
Great coffee and breakfast .
Santos Anne is mostly great for its awesome vibe, wood everywhere and great musicians playing often. The drinks are good and the menu looks great but the  food doesn't live up to its descriptions.

Most amazing atmosphere, so cozy and comfortable. French/ Mexican cuisine is really tasty, the steak brochette is my fave but the risotto and mussels are wonderful too. I'd go with wine here over the mixed drinks and stop by on open mic night or when they have free tarot readings. Best date spot!
Love the food!
Excellent margaritas. Had a seasonal pumpkin and a traditional, both were great.
Love the food.   Delicious desserts.   Also there are free tarot card reading on Monday.
Awesome backyard, pitchers of margerita and good Mexican Food.
Escargot is exceptional. Great live music!
Great atmosphere !
Cozy place

French and Mexican food mixed together with cosy ambiance inside withb live music or tarot reading and great backyard.
Lovely backyard with great food and a couple of interesting beers.
Great ambiance, brunch was tasty and the hosts were friendly. Perfect for a sunny clear day with their rustic and cozy backyard!
Great brunch. Nice outdoor garden at back
Excellent food and service! The duck burger tastes amazing.

Really enjoyed brunch here. I had the habanero margarita and huevos con chorizo. Nice and spicy, but not overwhelming. Also enjoyed the coffee that they serve to you in a large press - good for a group.  Recommended!
Nice backyard and friendly staff. Food was a little bland.

Interesting food, but the service was super super slow.
Food is fine, sort of in between Mexican and bistro, but not really doing either justice. Space is cute and staff is sweet

Amazing food, warm and friendly service. Delicious margaritas (wide variety of seasonal/rotating cocktails) and romantic atmosphere. Take your girl on a date here because it's casual enough but still nice and it will seem like you tried and thought about it.
Really nice restaurant, very good food, nice people, nice backyard... IT'S NICE
Live Band, Great Atmosphere, Large Outdoor Seating, Great Food
Favorite spot in Brooklyn. Great food, beautiful setting out the back, and awesome live music.
Great place
I love that place!! Best service, food and atmosphere!
Very good restaurant! Tried the Santos burger and was excellent! Also very nice margaritas! Oh and the owners are French so if you are too you'll probably have a nice chat with them!

One of my first Williamsburg dates with my now roommate and lover was here. It was a grand time in the pretty backyard with great drinks and even better service! Love this place. They're always giving out free shots and have interesting events happening. I had my tarot cards read as I ate brunch.
I love their steak tartare with the side of fries and salad. Their guacamole with shrimp and pineapple is really good, but could be better. This place is consistently great. I love living by here!
Great place with beautiful backyard and good food ! Happy hour margs are $5 !!
The best burger in NYC. Was such a treat. Great atmosphere and friendly staff.
Amazing food and drink!

An absolute treat! the atmosphere, the music, the food, the service..5 stars across the board. I'm not sure if the older french dude is the owner but he is absolutely the sweetest! He always hooks it up with free shots if we bring in a huge party and he is amazingly attentive. The pork and huevos rancheros are to die for! They'll usually have a live band playing some really relaxing, mellow tunes - so its a perfect date place or a party place (beautiful backyard).

I came here with a Scoutmob deal. A friend and I split two tasty dishes and had a couple of drinks. The outdoor seating area was very comfortable, albeit a little bit crowded, and our waiter was friendly (although clearly a little overwhelmed by the number of customers).

I love Santos Anne. This place has a very adorable ambiance, and is perfect for dates or for going out with friends. The food is fabulous, i particularly love their mushroom risotto flambe! Also, this is the best part, on monday nights they have this quirky awesome tarot reading! The guy who does the tarot readings is so cool, and he spends like a good 10 minutes giving you a thorough reading! Im not like normally a believer in tarot, but after a few drinks its soooo much fun to have the reading done. And they are surprisingly accurate....ahahaha. Love santos anne!

Santos Anne is a great place for any occasion. I went there with my boyfriend and he absolutely loved their steak. My salmon burger was delicious as well. This place does like mexican and french fusion and all of their mexican dishes are awesome. I am a big fan of the veggie tacos with goat cheese and porcini mushrooms! Great for a first date, especially if you go on a monday night because they do free tarot card readings!
Excellent drinks and service. Food was pleasant enough, just not memorable. Lovely back yard, good music, and more than reasonable prices. Definitely a good neighborhood go-to.

Best brunch experience in East Williamsburg. The place has comely interior decor and a lovelier back yard. The Mex-American brunch was all delicious. I had chorizo there twice in one weekend. We ordered two rouds of margaritas, and the waitress brought our shots for free to follow up on the meal.  (Update) I had to bump the food up to excellent after trying their burger with Chorizo mixed in.
Good food. Good decor!
